 &reftitle.setup;



  &reftitle.required;

PECL/stomp requires PHP 5.2.2 or newer.

The OpenSSL package >= 0.9.6 and the openssl extension may also be required to use stomp over SSL.




  &reftitle.install;


   &pecl.info;
   &url.pecl.package;stomp



   Quick installation 


    The Stomp extension is supplied as a PECL module, which you should be able to download and install in one step as follows:


$ pecl install stomp


    This will download the source, compile, and install stomp.so into your extension_dir. Make sure that the module is loaded by PHP, by adding following line to php.ini: 


extension=stomp.so







 &reference.stomp.ini;





  &reftitle.resources;


    There is only one resource type used in the stomp extension - it's
    the link identifier for a stomp connection.
